        X
        .
      
    
    {\displaystyle X.}
   That is, a filter on 
  
    
      
        X
      
    
    {\displaystyle X}
   is a filter-grill if and only if it is ultra. For any non-empty 
  
    
      
        
          
            F
          
        
        ⊆
        ℘
        (
        X
        )
        ,
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\mathcal {F}}\subseteq \wp (X),}
   
  
    
      
        
          
