        {
        y
        ∈
        X
         
        :
         
        (
        a
        ,
        y
        )
        ∈
        S
        }
        .
      
    
    {\displaystyle S{\big \vert }_{\{a\}\times X}:=\{y\in X~:~(a,y)\in S\}.}
   If 
  
    
      
        
          
            U
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\mathcal {U}}}
   is an ultrafilter on 
  
    
      
        X
      
    
    {\displaystyle X}
   then the set of all 
  
    
      
        S
        ⊆
        X
        ×
        X
      
    
    {\displaystyle S\subseteq X\times X}
   such that 
  
    
      
        
          {
          
